<sect1 id="kslovar-creating-dict">
<title>Creating a dictionary with &kslovar;</title>
<para>First click New dictionary button in File. Into the name field you type in the name of the dictionary. Then select a language,
if your language is not present, then you can create it. Into First page field you describe your new dictionary. After filling the
information, press enter and save the dictionary.</para>
</sect1>

<sect2 id="kslovar-editing-dict">
<title>Editing a dictionarey</title>
<para>By clicking on Edit->Edit dictionary you can edit a dicionary. The dialog is the same as with creating a dictionary.</para>
</sect2>

<sect3 id="kslovar-creating-lang">
<title>Creating a new language</title>
<para>If you click on the add button, there should be a dialog with the name and parts of speech fields empty. Fill in the information
about your language and press ok.</para>
</sect3>

<sect4 id="kslovar-editing-conversion">
<title>Editing the conversion table</title>
<para>In Settings->Edit converion table you can add or remve conversion characters. This conversion table is used only in search.</para>
</sect4>

<sect5 id="kslovar-creating-phrase">
<title>Creating a phrase</title>
<para>After making a dictionary you can create a phrase by Edit->Add phrase or right clicking on the phrase list on the left and
selecting Add phrase. After clicking the button, there should appear a dialog with 4 tabs. Fill in all the information about the phrase
and select synonyms, antonyms and word families. After filling in the information, click on ok to save the phrase.</para>
</sect5>

<sect6 id="kslovar-editing-phrase">
<title>Editing a phrase</title>
<para>You can edit a phrase by right clicking on it and click on the Edit phrase button. Or by selecting a phrase and clicking on
Edit->Edit phrase or just by double clicking on a phrase. The apeared dialog is the same as when creating a phrase.</para>
</sect6>

<sect7 id="kslovar-removing-phrase">
<title>Removing a phrase</title>
<para>You can remove a phrase by right clicking on a phrase and click Remove phrase or by selecting a phrase and clicking on
Edit->Remove phrase.</para>
</sect7>
</chapter>

<chapter id="dictionaries">
<title>Dictionaries and languages</title>
<sect1 id="send-it">
<title>Help apritiated<title>
<para>If you made your own language or dictionary file. Please send it to me at my mail, gregor@podnapisi.net so I could put it
on the page. Later in the development, the process of upload will be automated.</para>
</sect1>
</chapter>

